{{flavour|A ring that brings its wearer more in contact with the powers of ice. It grants resistance to cold and enhances ice magic, but causes vulnerability to heat.}}

A [[ring of ice]] is a [[ring]] that enhances the [[spell power|power]] of [[ice magic]] spells. Additionally, it provides one level of [[cold resistance]] (rC+) and one negative level of [[fire resistance]] (rF-).

==Tips & Tricks==
*A ring of ice can serve as a poor man's [[ring of protection from cold]] in a pinch, particularly if you should encounter an [[Ice Cave]] mini branch.
*You don't want to be vulnerable to any element for too long, since you (the player) can always forget about it. Even if you use [[Ice Magic]], you'll want a source of [[fire resistance]] to counteract the vulnerability. 
:If you don't have a way to negate rF-, Ice specialists can still find this ring useful - just remember to remove it against fiery enemies.

==History==
Prior to [[0.19]], rings of ice acted as a negative [[Fire Magic]] enhancer.

